{"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"LINK","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lissajous_curve","rel":"noopener","target":"blank"}}},"blocks":[{"key":"li01","text":"Similar to spirographs, but not to be confused with spirographs, a Lissajous curve is the graph of a system of parametric equations, which describe complex harmonic motion. Here, you can tweak the parameters of the lissajous curve drawing animation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"li02","text":"Below you will see an animation showing Lissajous curves. A and B each represent a speed that a dot moves around a circle. In one curve, the A dot represents the X axis movement, and the B dot represents the Y axis. In the other, the inverse is true; B ~ X and A ~ Y.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"li03","text":"Wikipedia Reference for Lissajous curve","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":39,"key":0}],"data":{}}]}
